data.body:
text editor decorations allow setting values like color, background color, etc.

An extension may create several decorations that share common values that should change together. Or even a single long-lived decoration that may change over time.

Currently making a change to those values requires creating a new decoration OR using render options which is warned against in the docs for performance reasons.

An alternative would be to allow extensions to set [custom css properties](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/--*). This would cause all decorations using this property to automatically update.

For example:
```javascript
// Set an initial background color
vscode.window.setCustomCssProperty('--my-extension-background-color', 'green');
// Create the decoration with the background color set to reference a custom css property
vscode.window.createTextEditorDecorationType({ backgroundColor: 'var(--my-extension-background-color)' });
...
// Something happens that should change the background color
vscode.window.setCustomCssProperty('--my-extension-background-color', 'red');
```
